            "courseCode": "APL-BTC-H-002",
            "courseName": "skill set",
            "courseDescription": "<p>My core skillset is centered around semantic HTML5 and modern CSS3, with a strong emphasis on writing clean, accessible, and maintainable markup. I structure content using meaningful elements like section, article, nav, and header to ensure logical document outlines and strong SEO foundations. My understanding of accessibility goes beyond basic alt text; I implement proper ARIA labels, focus management, and landmark roles to ensure interfaces are fully usable for screen reader and keyboard-only users. I treat HTML as the structural skeleton of the application, ensuring that the page remains functional and readable even before a single line of CSS is applied.\r\n\r\nOn the styling side, my CSS workflow is built around responsive design principles and scalable architecture. I leverage Flexbox and CSS Grid interchangeably to solve complex layout challenges, whether it's a dynamic card grid that reflows seamlessly or a sticky footer that stays put. I am proficient in writing modular CSS using methodologies like BEM (Block Element Modifier) or utility-first approaches to prevent specificity wars and keep stylesheets lean. Furthermore, I have deep experience with CSS custom properties for managing design tokens, and I utilize advanced selectors and pseudo-elements to reduce reliance on extraneous div containers.\r\n\r\nMy skillset extends to creating performant, polished user interfaces with meticulous attention to detail. I handle cross-browser compatibility issues proactively, ensuring that modern features like aspect-ratio or backdrop-filter degrade gracefully in older engines. I am comfortable building complex animations and micro-interactions using @keyframes, transitions, and the will-change property to maintain silky-smooth 60fps performance. This foundation in pure HTML and CSS allows me to collaborate effectively with JavaScript engineers, providing a robust, style-agnostic layer that is easy to extend and refactor as project requirements evolve.</p>",
            "courseDuration": "",
            "courseLevel": "Beginner",
